---

## What the test suite covers

| Category | Tests | Requirement coverage |
|---|---|---|
| **Registered device – happy path** | 201 returned, Observation in body, server ID assigned, sequential & parallel pushes, multiple LOINC types | "shall push Observations" |
| **Unregistered device – rejection** | 401 / 403 returned, OperationOutcome body, no 201 ever returned, empty/malformed tokens, repeated attempts | "unregistered devices shall be rejected" |
| **Boundary / edge cases** | Revoked token, missing device reference, mismatched device ID, wrong resource type, empty body | Robustness around the registration boundary |

### Key design decisions
* **`FHIRIngestClient`** is a minimal interface shim – swap `patch.object` for real HTTP calls (e.g. `requests`) when running against a live environment.  
* All server interactions are mocked with `unittest.mock.patch.object`, keeping tests fast and deterministic.  
* `@pytest.mark.parametrize` covers the full range of required vital-sign Observation types without duplicating test logic.  
* Thread-safety is validated with `concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor`.

